<section id="To_edit_the_Default_States_Instance" remap="TID_15566">
	<title>Editing the Default State Instance</title>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Edit the Default State Instance</title> 
		<!--step>
			<para>
				Log in as a user with admin or super administrator rights to the <productname>CloudForms Management Engine</productname> console.
			</para>
		</step-->
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Automate</guimenu><guisubmenu>Explorer</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step> 
		<!--<step>
			<para>
				From the accordion menu, click <menuchoice><guimenu>Datastore</guimenu><guisubmenu>Factory</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>StateMachines</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>VMProvision State Machine (VMProvision_VM)</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Provision VM from Template (template)</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step> -->
		<step>
			<para>
				From the accordion menu, click <menuchoice><guimenu>DOMAIN</guimenu><guisubmenu>Cloud</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>VM</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Provisioning</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>StateMachines</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>VMProvision_VM</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.
			</para>
			<note>
				<para>
					DOMAIN must be a user-defined Domain and not the locked ManageIQ Domain. If necessary, you can copy the class from the ManageIQ domain into a custom domain.
				</para>
				<para>
					This example uses the <guilabel>Cloud</guilabel> Namespace but can also use the <guilabel>Infrastructure</guilabel> namespace.
				</para>
			</note>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Configuration)</guilabel>, then 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1851.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guilabel>(Edit this instance)</guilabel>.
			</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/6281.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				For each step that you want to remove, clear the entries in the <guilabel>Value</guilabel>, <guilabel>On Entry</guilabel>, <guilabel>On Exit</guilabel>, and <guilabel>On Error</guilabel> columns.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Save</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>